Process called "powerpc_optimize_instruction_sequence" takes instructions_ptr as Integer, count as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Peephole optimizer over an already-encoded instruction-record sequence, using
    Note: the same 32-byte record layout as the other platform delegates (four
    Note: little-endian 8-byte fields: opcode_id, operand_a, operand_b, operand_c).
    Note: Running on the operation records (not raw bytes) keeps peepholes valid for
    Note: the fixed-width PowerPC ISA.
    Note: ---
    Note: Implemented peephole (semantics-preserving on PowerPC):
    Note:   Redundant self-move elimination: MOV rd, rd (opcode 1, operand_a ==
    Note:   operand_b) is `mr rd, rd` (OR rd, r0... alias), a true no-op. It is
    Note:   rewritten in place to NOP (opcode 9). Because powerpc_encode_instruction
    Note:   reports NOP as unavailable on this target, a later assembly pass drops the
    Note:   opcode-9 records entirely rather than emitting them; rewriting to 9
    Note:   (instead of physical removal) preserves the record count and any branch
    Note:   offsets until that drop pass runs.
    Note: PUSH/POP round-trip elimination is intentionally not applied on PowerPC
    Note: because per-register push/pop is not realized on this target (stack traffic
    Note: is frame-based; see PUSH/POP GAP above).
    Note: Returns the number of records rewritten (0 when already optimal -- correct
    Note: identity behavior).
    Let optimized_count be 0
    Let i be 0
    Let record_size be 32
    While i is less than count:
        Let base be instructions_ptr plus (i multiplied by record_size)
        Let opcode_id be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with base, 0
        Let operand_a be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with base, 8
        Let operand_b be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with base, 16
        If opcode_id is equal to 1:
            If operand_a is equal to operand_b:
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with base, 0, 9
                Set optimized_count to optimized_count plus 1
            End If
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return optimized_count
End Process